definitions.definition: An instance or the act of yielding nothing.
examples: We've had one strikeout after the other on the Jones account.

definitions.definition: An instance or the act of striking out.
examples: The pitcher recorded seven strikeouts in the game.

definitions.definition: Cancellation of a portion of text by crossing it out without deleting it; strikethrough .

main_definition: ( countable ) An instance or the act of yielding nothing.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , baseball ) An instance or the act of striking out.
( computing , wordprocessing ) Cancellation of a portion of text by crossing it out without deleting it; strikethrough .
